	<body>
		<outline title="<![CDATA[Digital Magic]]>" xmlUrl="http://feeds.feedburner.com/DigitalMagic" type="rss" htmlUrl="http://www.digitalmagicnovel.com/?cat=4" text="<![CDATA[Digital Magic by Philippa J. Ballantine &ndash; Where the Future &amp; Fey Collide]]>" description="<![CDATA[<h1>Digital Magic is the sequel to Chasing the Bard- the award winning podcast novel–written by New Zealand author Philippa Ballantine.</h1><p>Penherem is a quaint, sleepy English village where people go to escape the 21st Century.&nbsp; Hiding from the world of laptop computers, the Internet, and wireless communication, is Ella.&nbsp; A writer, now barren of ideas and drive, she resigns herself to a quiet life of solitude.&nbsp; Everything changes with the arrival of a shapeshifting thief.&nbsp; Suddenly, everyone begins to change–from the local librarian to the lady of the manor–revealing their true natures and dangerous secrets.&nbsp; Something in this sleepy English village is awakening… something that might be better left alone.</p>]]>"/>
		<outline title="<![CDATA[Weaver&apos;s Web (via Podiobooks.com)]]>" xmlUrl="http://www.podiobooks.com/title/weavers-web/" type="rss" text="<![CDATA[Weaver&apos;s Web - A free audiobook by P.J. Ballantine]]>" htmlUrl="http://www.podiobooks.com/title/weavers-web/" description="<![CDATA[Betrayal by one you love is the cruelest cut of all.&nbsp; And when the Lord of Crisfell betrays it is done on a grand scale.&nbsp; Ashi&apos;mei Candre feels her life is destroyed in that instant, but her love&apos;s betrayal goes far further- he is sacrificing his own people.&nbsp; Amongst the islands of Crisfell, honour and clan is everything, but that may also be their undoing.&nbsp; A dark secret from the past will now come back with a vengeance, and Ashi&apos;mei must put her own troubles aside to face this greater danger.&nbsp; For over the dark sea is a menace of flesh and hunger, which having been turned back once, is only more determined to remake Crisfell in its image.&nbsp; When the danger comes from within as well as without, Ashi&apos;mei&apos;s world is doomed.&nbsp; And yet there are two from beyond the island who may help, one a passionate young man from their traditional enemy, and the other a compelling creature with mastery of the flesh to rival the menace beyond the sea.&nbsp; With friends and clan her only hope, the time to stand and fight has come.&nbsp; Ashi&apos;mei must search within herself for salvation for her people, face her darkest fears, and risk everything she loves.]]>"/>
		<outline title="<![CDATA[Chasing the Bard]]>" xmlUrl="http://feeds.feedburner.com/ChasingTheBard" type="rss" text="<![CDATA[Chasing the Bard]]>" htmlUrl="http://www.chasingthebard.com" description="<![CDATA[Shakespeare ventures in his own midsummer nightmare, where a dark goddess plots to use his bardic powers to save her world- if he likes it or not.&nbsp; Follow Shakespeare in to the Fey.&nbsp; Follow ]]>" />
		<outline title="<![CDATA[Chasing the Bard (via Podiobooks.com)]]>" xmlUrl="http://www.podiobooks.com/title/chasing-the-bard/feed/" text="<![CDATA[Chasing the Bard - A free audiobook by Philippa J. Ballantine]]>" htmlUrl="http://www.podiobooks.com/title/chasing-the-bard/" description="<![CDATA[Born into the human world with a gift; a gift that brings him to the attention of powers both dark and light from the World of the Fey, it is his burden to defend all the world.&nbsp; Sive, the goddess of battle, hopes that he may be able to change the fate of her people.&nbsp; The Fey are dying, killed by something beyond the boundaries of worlds, and Sive will do anything to save them.&nbsp; So she  enlists the help of her trickster cousin Puck to guard the child, and  watch him grow into his gift.&nbsp; But a dark power imprisoned by human  and Fey, plots to destroy both worlds, and unmake all that they have  created.&nbsp; Can one boy stop the destruction, even if he is William Shakespeare?]]>"/>
		<outline title="<![CDATA[Weather Child]]>" xmlUrl="http://weatherchild.com/feed/" type="rss" text="<![CDATA[Weather Child]]>" htmlUrl="http://weatherchild.com" description="<![CDATA[Step back in time and sideways into an alternate world, where magicians and seraphim are found only on the shores of the Long White Cloud.&nbsp; Between two world wars, Jack and Faith find themselves unravelling a conspiracy to turn the Awakened children of . . . A fantasy alternate history of New Zealand.]]>" />
		<outline title="<![CDATA[Erotica a la carte &#187; The Stories (RSS2 Feed)]]>" xmlUrl="http://www.eroticaalacarte.com/category/the-stories/feed/" type="rss" text="<![CDATA[Erotica a la carte &#187; The Stories (RSS2 Feed)]]>" htmlUrl="http://www.eroticaalacarte.com" description="<![CDATA[<h1>Erotica a la carte</h1><h2>The Stories (RSS2 Feed)</h2><p>Fantasy erotica, created monthly from listeners&apos; survey.</p><p>An experiment in short story writing. Award nominated speculative fiction writer and award winning podcaster, P J Ballantine and invited guest chefs will offer a saucy menu to listeners from the erotica a la carte kitchen.</p><p>Here are the rules of the restaurant.</p><p>The chefs will produce a menu which will be posted on the 15th of each month.</p><p>It will stay up until 15th of the next month, when the listeners choices will be delivered to the chef.</p><p>The chef will then have another month to write and produce the podcast.</p><p>Each story will be speculative fiction- fantasy, science fiction or horror- and will be at most 5,000 words in length.</p>]]>" />
		<outline title="<![CDATA[Erotica a la carte &#187; The Stories (Atom feed)]]>" xmlUrl="http://www.eroticaalacarte.com/category/the-stories/feed/atom/" type="rss" text="<![CDATA[Erotica a la carte &#187; The Stories (Atom feed)]]>" htmlUrl="http://www.eroticaalacarte.com" description="<![CDATA[<h1>Erotica a la carte</h1><h2>The Stories (Atom feed)</h2><p>Fantasy erotica, created monthly from listeners&apos; survey.</p><p>An experiment in short story writing. Award nominated speculative fiction writer and award winning podcaster, P J Ballantine and invited guest chefs will offer a saucy menu to listeners from the erotica a la carte kitchen.</p><p>Here are the rules of the restaurant.</p><p>The chefs will produce a menu which will be posted on the 15th of each month.</p><p>It will stay up until 15th of the next month, when the listeners choices will be delivered to the chef.</p><p>The chef will then have another month to write and produce the podcast.</p><p>Each story will be speculative fiction- fantasy, science fiction or horror- and will be at most 5,000 words in length.</p>]]>" />
